**Most critical gap**: `handle_filesystem_callback` (red-cell-c2-abm8) — 9 out of 10 filesystem subcommands (Dir, Upload, Cd, Remove, Mkdir, Copy, Move, GetPwd, Cat) have absolutely zero test coverage at any level. Any parsing error in these handlers silently produces garbage operator output.

**Overall test quality**: The core infrastructure (agents, auth, api, database, audit) is well-tested with meaningful assertions. The weak spots are concentrated in the `dispatch/` sub-handlers where individual command processors lack unit tests and rely entirely on large integration tests in `dispatch/mod.rs` — which only cover a subset of subcommand variants.
